eastwards through much of Central and Southern Europe into European parts of 
<collectingCountry id="F5B1EBC9320CFFF45FD202CFFBE6FD12" box="[966,1042,694,720]" name="Russia" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Russia</collectingCountry>
Transcaucasus; 
<collectingCountry id="F5B1EBC9320CFFF45CB202AEFF2CFD33" box="[166,216,727,753]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E937D6A8320CFFF45CF302AFFDFDFD33" author="Khaghaninia, S. &amp; Farshbaf &amp; Pour Abad, R. &amp; Hayat, R." box="[231,521,726,753]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" pagination="307 - 308" refId="ref6660" refString="Khaghaninia, S., Farshbaf, Pour Abad, R., Hayat, R. Seven species as new records for hoverflies fauna of Iran (Diptera: Syrphidae) from Qaradag forests // Munis Entomology and Zoology. - 2010. - 5, N 1. - P. 307 - 308." type="book chapter" year="2010">Khaghaninia et al., 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D19AB59320CFFF45CCF028EFC36FC73" blockId="2.[166,1225,662,945]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">
D i a g n o s t i c c h a r a c t e r s. Eye with pale hairs in apical half; third antennal segment entirely or mostly yellowish-orange (
<figureCitation id="159DB7DC320CFFF45E73036FFD53FCF2" box="[615,679,790,816]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[170,203,1674,1696]" captionTargetBox="[176,1228,642,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-285@3.[170,1229,636,1646]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Cheilosia aerea (a–c): a — dorsal view of female, b — lateral view of head of female, c — male genitalia; C. cumanica (d–f): d — dorsal view of female, e — frontal view of head of female, f — male genitalia; C. lola, female (g–h): g — dorsal view, h — frontal view of head. Рис. 1. Cheilosia aerea (a–c): a — самка, вид сверху; b — голова самки, латеральный вид, c — гениталии самца; C. cumanica (d–f): d — самка, вид сверху, e — голова самки, фронтальный вид, f — гениталии самца; C. lola, самка (g–h): g — вид сверху, h — голова, фронтальный вид." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449151/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="BFD2774B320CFFF45EAC036FFD32FCF2" box="[696,710,790,816]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">b</emphasis>
); face without distinct hairs (microtrichia not taken into account); median facial tubercle sharply convex; mesoscutum with coarse punctuation; posterior margin of scutellum with black or yellow bristles distinctly more robust than surrounding hairs (
<figureCitation id="159DB7DC320CFFF45E09030FFDAEFC52" box="[541,602,886,912]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[170,203,1674,1696]" captionTargetBox="[176,1228,642,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-285@3.[170,1229,636,1646]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Cheilosia aerea (a–c): a — dorsal view of female, b — lateral view of head of female, c — male genitalia; C. cumanica (d–f): d — dorsal view of female, e — frontal view of head of female, f — male genitalia; C. lola, female (g–h): g — dorsal view, h — frontal view of head. Рис. 1. Cheilosia aerea (a–c): a — самка, вид сверху; b — голова самки, латеральный вид, c — гениталии самца; C. cumanica (d–f): d — самка, вид сверху, e — голова самки, фронтальный вид, f — гениталии самца; C. lola, самка (g–h): g — вид сверху, h — голова, фронтальный вид." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449151/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="BFD2774B320CFFF45E7C030EFD82FC52" box="[616,630,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">a</emphasis>
); fore coxa without tooth, at least first segment of mid tarsus or bases of tibiae yellowish; male genitalia as in (
<figureCitation id="159DB7DC320CFFF45F4A03EFFC6DFC72" box="[862,921,918,944]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[170,203,1674,1696]" captionTargetBox="[176,1228,642,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-285@3.[170,1229,636,1646]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Cheilosia aerea (a–c): a — dorsal view of female, b — lateral view of head of female, c — male genitalia; C. cumanica (d–f): d — dorsal view of female, e — frontal view of head of female, f — male genitalia; C. lola, female (g–h): g — dorsal view, h — frontal view of head. Рис. 1. Cheilosia aerea (a–c): a — самка, вид сверху; b — голова самки, латеральный вид, c — гениталии самца; C. cumanica (d–f): d — самка, вид сверху, e — голова самки, фронтальный вид, f — гениталии самца; C. lola, самка (g–h): g — вид сверху, h — голова, фронтальный вид." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449151/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="BFD2774B320CFFF45FB203EEFC45FC72" box="[934,945,919,944]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">c</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
